data.description: Do not miss this home in the quiet village of Huntzdale. This three-bedroom, two full-bath home has recently been updated. The main floor has a nice size kitchen with room for a breakfast nook. The large dining room has lots of windows giving lots of natural lighting. A great space for hosting dinner parties. The dining room has an open flow into the living room. The living room has built-in benches for extra storage, be great for games or hunting/fishing gear. The living room has a propane stove for extra coziness on those chilly winter nights. The living room has two exits too outside. one is sliding doors to a covered back patio and a huge fenced-in yard. Plenty of yards for cookouts. The second exit in the living room is French doors to the carport/breezeway to the garage. The main bedroom is on the first floor and has a big closet, a large full private bathroom with a laundry hookup. Upstairs has two nice size bedrooms and a big newly updated full bathroom. Upstairs bedrooms, both have newer carpets and closets. The huge fenced-in back yard has views of the fish hatchery. The beautiful Yellow Breeches Creek runs behind the property, a nationally known trout stream. The two-bay garage is heated with ceiling mounted propane heater great for the mechanic or for hobbies. Blacktop driveway to the carport and in front of the garage with lots of extra stone parking beside the garage and behind the garage. This home is minutes from I-81 for an easy commute. It is convenient for all your shopping needs, right outside Newville, Carlisle and Shippensburg. If you love nature you will enjoy the short drive to Kings Gap, Pine Grove Furnace State Parks, Laurel and Fuller Lakes. This home is perfect if you want small-town, country living. This home will go fast, so call me today to make this home yours!
